    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"氏 represents the fundamental importance of family lineage and ancestral identity in Chinese\nculture. It reflects the Confucian emphasis on family relationships and the continuity of\nbloodlines. In traditional China, one's 氏 determined social status, marriage possibilities, and\nspiritual obligations to ancestors, making it central to personal and social identity."}],"type":"paragraph"}
